main event: An irregular-shaped object, approximately 35 feet across with trails of light behind it, was observed moving slowly across the sky in Wilmington, North Carolina on August 5, 1960.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 10 minutes, and was first seen from a pine-covered area on a dirt road.
The object was observed to fall or tumble to the ground, disappearing into heavy brush and swampy ground behind trees.
A power company lineman had initially notified authorities about the object falling.
The object was observed at an elevation just under the cloud coverage, and disappeared at an elevation of approximately 22 degrees.
The weather was partly cloudy with no wind, and visibility was good at 15 miles.
sighted object: Irregular shaped object approximately 35 feet across with trails of light
